text: María Álvarez (born 10 October 1989) is a Colombian swimmer. She competed in the women's 200 metre freestyle at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. ==References== Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Colombian female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2015 Pan American Games Category:Swimmers at the 2019 Pan American Games
